cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics in medical interventions, specifically in robot-assisted retinal microsurgery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of a robot-controlled surgical tool, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper proposes a novel deep learning method for detecting and recognizing keypoints in high definition images, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of smoothness constraints in the 3D reconstruction pipeline could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
